						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Steven Levy</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">This article is about the American technology writer.  For the New York politician, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Levy_(politician)" title="Steve Levy (politician)">Steve Levy (politician)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Steven_Levy_Author.JPG" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Steven_Levy_Author.JPG/220px-Steven_Levy_Author.JPG" width="220" height="292" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Steven_Levy_Author.JPG/330px-Steven_Levy_Author.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Steven_Levy_Author.JPG/440px-Steven_Levy_Author.JPG 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Steven_Levy_Author.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.23wmf18/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Steven Levy</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Steven Levy</b> (born 1951) is an <a href="United_States.html" title="United States">American</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journalist" title="Journalist">journalist</a> who has written several books on computers, technology, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography" title="Cryptography">cryptography</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_internet" title="The internet" class="mw-redirect">the internet</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cybersecurity" title="Cybersecurity" class="mw-redirect">cybersecurity</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Privacy" title="Privacy">privacy</a>.</p>
<p></p>
